description.narrative:
Implementation Phase (1st September to 31st December 2021)
- Delivery of tailor-made technical assistance for Burundi, to develop capacity in advanced Post Clearance Audit techniques;
 - Roadmap to support the EAC region to conduct regional Time Release Studies (TRS) is 
established;
 - Beneficiary countries in SADC region have set the foundations (commitment, technical working group, and cooperation with SADC Secretariat) to commence the development of a regional framework for Customs connectivity and data exchange;
- Terms of Reference developed to support Botswana in recruitment of Expert(s) to conduct 
Readiness Assessment of the national Single Window project;
- Terms of Reference for the Eswatini Trader Connect Solution developed;
- Delivery of joint awareness and capacity building to support Zimbabwe and Uganda on Gender Equality and Inclusion imperatives for Customs, and the approaches to implement gender equality policies and practices;
- Delivery of 3 respective national awareness and sensitization workshops on the Basel Convention and Montreal Protocol, for Customs and the national environment agencies of Botswana, Malawi and Rwanda; and
- Development of draft work plan and budget for the period 1 January 2022 to 31 December 2022.
